<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E7BFFF548F75669FC15FD8D" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="007606418E7BFFF548F75669FC15FD8D" blockId="53.[150,1437,288,746]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E7BFFF548F75669FEE4FEAE" bold="true" box="[199,321,325,350]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E7BFFF549795669FE38FEAD" box="[329,413,325,349]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Female</emphasis>
: fully winged (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E7BFFF54A7D5669FD7BFEAD" box="[589,734,325,349]" captionStart="PLATE 16" captionStartId="57.[151,233,1428,1451]" captionTargetBox="[163,1414,210,1383]" captionTargetId="figure-206@57.[151,1436,193,1407]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="PLATE 16. Fiorianteon rugosum. A, B. Holotype, dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B) (from Olmi 1991). Length 2.9 mm. C. Chela of holotype (from Olmi 1991). D. Male genitalia of male from China, Taiwan (from Olmi 1995a). Scale bar 0.17 mm for C and 0.20 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278426/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Plate 16A, B</figureCitation>
); occipital carina complete; mandible quadridentate, with one intermediate rudimentary tooth (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E7BFFF54A325645FDC5FE71" box="[514,608,361,385]" captionStart="PLATE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,233,1838,1861]" captionTargetBox="[163,1415,270,1746]" captionTargetId="figure-69@10.[151,1436,253,1777]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="PLATE 3. A–C, F, G. Males. D, E. Mandibles. A. Crovettia sp. Length 2.5 mm. B. Fiorianteon sp. Length 3.8 mm. C. Dryinus sp. Length 3.7 mm. D. Anteon sp., Female. E. Dryinidae. F. Thaumatodryinus sp. Length 1.9 mm. G. Anteon sp. Length 2.5 mm. (From Olmi 1984)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278380/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Plate 3E</figureCitation>
); antenna without rhinaria; palpal formula 6/3; pronotal tubercles present; fore wing with two cells enclosed by pigmented veins (costal and median) (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E7BFFF54BC056A1FB27FE55" box="[1008,1154,397,421]" captionStart="PLATE 16" captionStartId="57.[151,233,1428,1451]" captionTargetBox="[163,1414,210,1383]" captionTargetId="figure-206@57.[151,1436,193,1407]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="PLATE 16. Fiorianteon rugosum. A, B. Holotype, dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B) (from Olmi 1991). Length 2.9 mm. C. Chela of holotype (from Olmi 1991). D. Male genitalia of male from China, Taiwan (from Olmi 1995a). Scale bar 0.17 mm for C and 0.20 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278426/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Plate 16A, B</figureCitation>
); fore wing with stigmal vein and pterostigma present (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E7BFFF549C2569DFD23FE39" box="[498,646,433,457]" captionStart="PLATE 16" captionStartId="57.[151,233,1428,1451]" captionTargetBox="[163,1414,210,1383]" captionTargetId="figure-206@57.[151,1436,193,1407]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="PLATE 16. Fiorianteon rugosum. A, B. Holotype, dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B) (from Olmi 1991). Length 2.9 mm. C. Chela of holotype (from Olmi 1991). D. Male genitalia of male from China, Taiwan (from Olmi 1995a). Scale bar 0.17 mm for C and 0.20 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278426/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Plate 16A, B</figureCitation>
); distal part of stigmal vein as long as, or shorter than proximal part (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E7BFFF5489056F9FE95FE1D" box="[160,304,469,493]" captionStart="PLATE 16" captionStartId="57.[151,233,1428,1451]" captionTargetBox="[163,1414,210,1383]" captionTargetId="figure-206@57.[151,1436,193,1407]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="PLATE 16. Fiorianteon rugosum. A, B. Holotype, dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B) (from Olmi 1991). Length 2.9 mm. C. Chela of holotype (from Olmi 1991). D. Male genitalia of male from China, Taiwan (from Olmi 1995a). Scale bar 0.17 mm for C and 0.20 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278426/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Plate 16A, B</figureCitation>
); protarsus chelate (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E7BFFF54A2456F9FD00FE1D" box="[532,677,469,493]" captionStart="PLATE 16" captionStartId="57.[151,233,1428,1451]" captionTargetBox="[163,1414,210,1383]" captionTargetId="figure-206@57.[151,1436,193,1407]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="PLATE 16. Fiorianteon rugosum. A, B. Holotype, dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B) (from Olmi 1991). Length 2.9 mm. C. Chela of holotype (from Olmi 1991). D. Male genitalia of male from China, Taiwan (from Olmi 1995a). Scale bar 0.17 mm for C and 0.20 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278426/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Plate 16A, B</figureCitation>
); chela with rudimentary claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E7BFFF54C3B56F9FBDDFE1D" box="[1035,1144,469,493]" captionStart="PLATE 16" captionStartId="57.[151,233,1428,1451]" captionTargetBox="[163,1414,210,1383]" captionTargetId="figure-206@57.[151,1436,193,1407]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="PLATE 16. Fiorianteon rugosum. A, B. Holotype, dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B) (from Olmi 1991). Length 2.9 mm. C. Chela of holotype (from Olmi 1991). D. Male genitalia of male from China, Taiwan (from Olmi 1995a). Scale bar 0.17 mm for C and 0.20 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278426/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Plate 16C</figureCitation>
); tibial spurs 1/1/2. 
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E7BFFF54D6B56F9FA31FE1D" box="[1371,1428,469,493]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Male</emphasis>
: fully winged (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E7BFFF5490556D5FE61FDE1" box="[309,452,505,529]" captionStart="PLATE 15" captionStartId="55.[151,233,1969,1992]" captionTargetBox="[157,1422,204,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-61@55.[151,1436,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="PLATE 15. Fiorianteon junonium. A. Chela of female from Japan, Mt. Tsukuba (from Olmi 1995a). B, C. Holotype, dorsal view (B) and lateral view (C) (from Olmi 1984). Length 3.8 mm. Scale bar 0.20 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278422/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Plate 15B, C</figureCitation>
); occipital carina complete; mandible quadridentate, with one intermediate rudimentary tooth (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E7BFFF548D35531FEE1FDC5" box="[227,324,541,565]" captionStart="PLATE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,233,1838,1861]" captionTargetBox="[163,1415,270,1746]" captionTargetId="figure-69@10.[151,1436,253,1777]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="PLATE 3. A–C, F, G. Males. D, E. Mandibles. A. Crovettia sp. Length 2.5 mm. B. Fiorianteon sp. Length 3.8 mm. C. Dryinus sp. Length 3.7 mm. D. Anteon sp., Female. E. Dryinidae. F. Thaumatodryinus sp. Length 1.9 mm. G. Anteon sp. Length 2.5 mm. (From Olmi 1984)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278380/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Plate 3E</figureCitation>
); palpal formula 6/3; fore wing with two cells enclosed by pigmented veins (costal and median) (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E7BFFF54890556DFE94FDA9" box="[160,305,577,601]" captionStart="PLATE 15" captionStartId="55.[151,233,1969,1992]" captionTargetBox="[157,1422,204,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-61@55.[151,1436,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="PLATE 15. Fiorianteon junonium. A. Chela of female from Japan, Mt. Tsukuba (from Olmi 1995a). B, C. Holotype, dorsal view (B) and lateral view (C) (from Olmi 1984). Length 3.8 mm. Scale bar 0.20 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278422/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Plate 15B, C</figureCitation>
); fore wing with stigmal vein and pterostigma present (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E7BFFF54B9E556DFB9AFDA9" box="[942,1087,577,601]" captionStart="PLATE 15" captionStartId="55.[151,233,1969,1992]" captionTargetBox="[157,1422,204,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-61@55.[151,1436,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="PLATE 15. Fiorianteon junonium. A. Chela of female from Japan, Mt. Tsukuba (from Olmi 1995a). B, C. Holotype, dorsal view (B) and lateral view (C) (from Olmi 1984). Length 3.8 mm. Scale bar 0.20 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278422/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Plate 15B, C</figureCitation>
); distal part of stigmal vein as long as, or shorter than proximal part (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E7BFFF54A775549FD73FD8D" box="[583,726,613,637]" captionStart="PLATE 15" captionStartId="55.[151,233,1969,1992]" captionTargetBox="[157,1422,204,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-61@55.[151,1436,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="PLATE 15. Fiorianteon junonium. A. Chela of female from Japan, Mt. Tsukuba (from Olmi 1995a). B, C. Holotype, dorsal view (B) and lateral view (C) (from Olmi 1984). Length 3.8 mm. Scale bar 0.20 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278422/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Plate 15B, C</figureCitation>
); tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E7BFFF548F755A5FCD1FD51" box="[199,884,649,674]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="007606418E7BFFF548F755A5FCD1FD51" blockId="53.[150,1437,288,746]" box="[199,884,649,674]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E7BFFF548F755A5FEC5FD52" bold="true" box="[199,352,649,674]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Distribution.</emphasis>
Present in the Palaearctic and 
